com.zensols.unix.userauth

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zensols.unix.userauth.Command

  • public class Command
extends Object
    Represents a command line executable program. It uses the path given to find the program, if it doesn't find it, it uses the which commandn line program.
    Author:
    Paul Landes

      • doExecute

        protected CommandOutput doExecute(Integer expectReturn,
                                  List<String> args,
                                  List<String> input)
                           throws SystemException,
                                  IOException
        Execute a program.
        Parameters:
        expectReturn - the integer expected and compared to the returned code from the command line program
        args - a list of arguments (including the program name) to execute
        input - new line separated string data to feed to the program through an IPC parent/child pipe if non-null
        Returns:
        the output from the command
        Throws:
        SystemException - if expectReturn is non-null and doesn't match what the program returns
        IOException - if any IO problems happened during execution via the IPC pipe

      • execute

        public CommandOutput execute(Integer expectReturn,
                             String args,
                             List<String> input)
                      throws SystemException
        Execute a program.
        Parameters:
        expectReturn - the integer expected and compared to the returned code from the command line program
        args - a space delimited set of arguments passed to the program
        input - new line separated string data to feed to the program through an IPC parent/child pipe if non-null
        Returns:
        the output from the command
        Throws:
        SystemException - if expectReturn is non-null and doesn't match what the program returns or any IO issues with the IPC child communication occured
